### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When creating a NonNullableFormBuilder it shouldn't let you assign default null value to FormControl's instanciated with it. 
Appart from this, even though i create the FormGroup with the NonNullableFormBuilder i still need to put the option **nonNullable: true** on each FormControl, else i the provided error TS2322, (can't reproduce this last error on the stackblitz example, but im getting it on the app im working on).

```
readonly formBuilder = inject<NonNullableFormBuilder>(NonNullableFormBuilder);

/**
error TS2322: Type 'FormControl<string | null>' is not assignable to type 'FormControl<string>'.
  Type 'string | null' is not assignable to type 'string'.
    Type 'null' is not assignable to type 'string'.

57             name: new FormControl('', {
**/
 const fb = this.formBuilder.group<PersonForm>({
      name: new FormControl( ' ', {
        validators: [Validators.required] //missing nonNullable: true
      }),
      firstName: new FormControl(
        { value: ' ', disabled: true },
        { validators: [Validators.required], nonNullable: true }
      ),
    });

//Getting same Type error if i set name default value to null
const fb = this.formBuilder.group<PersonForm>({
      name: new FormControl( null , {
        validators: [Validators.required], nonNullable: true
      }),
      firstName: new FormControl(
        { value: ' ', disabled: true },
        { validators: [Validators.required], nonNullable: true }
      ),
    });
```

